reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 17, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Efficient traveling bags
reviews.reviewText: These are amazing bags for traveling! I was a bit skeptical but I wanted something to help organize my things from my children’s things when we go on short trips; I tend to throw my little ones’ clothes into my suitcase along with my things so we have fewer bags to carry. These bags worked so well. They’re very well-made, you can feel the durability when you touch them, the zippers are smooth and the material is nice and thick. The quality of materials is impressive for the price. Plus, the color design is super cute!We used the laundry bags for my toddler’s toys, bedtime diapers, and toiletries. It was a more efficient use for us than utilizing them as actual laundry bags. My daughter loved the shoe bag.Overall, I loved this set! The price is perfect! This bag set feels and looks high-end, It looks like I paid a lot more than what I actually did. I ordered another bag configuration set from a different company and, although I paid more for it, it felt and looked cheaper than this set. This set looks great, I will be ordering more as gifts. 👍🏼👍🏼

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 21, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Expect So-So Craftsmanship
reviews.reviewText: UPDATE: I've changed my three-star rating to four. Cathy at Mossio emailed me to apologize for the state of my packing cubes, which was totally unexpected but appreciated. To my surprise, she offered a refund AND a new set of cubes. Although I indicated that they didn't have to, since I still have the cubes and plan to use them, she initiated a refund and a new set arrived on my doorstep within a couple of days.Cathy was friendly and responsive. If each of their customer service reps is like her, your inquiries and/or issues should be addressed swiftly and kindly.Once the SARS-CoV-2 pandemic is in the rearview mirror and I have an opportunity to use these cubes on a trip, I'll provide another update as to the cubes' ability to withstand use. Here's hopin' for a five-star sturdiness rating! :)~~~~~~~~~~I finally broke down and ordered packing cubes last night. I’d been wanting some for months but had always been concerned about durability and quality, so I sprang for these relatively inexpensive ones (easier be impressed?).They arrived this afternoon, and as I inspected them, the lower quality became apparent. One pouch had several rust-colored stains inside (a couple of stains those pictured here). Another had a fabric edge that the thread hadn’t caught (also pictured here). A couple of the zippers have imperfections (and aren’t YKK zippers—maybe the seller meant YKK-style zippers?).Either way, I was disappointed but not crushed. The seams seem sturdy enough, but I’ll have to update my review once I’ve had a chance to travel with them. On the bright side, the pattern is cute and the items are nice and lightweight.

reviews.reviewTitle: Depends on your usage, to be honest
reviews.reviewText: If you want it to sort the small clothes and accessories (apart from the main clothes) to keep them separate in a trolley during travel, maybe this is for you. The boxes are that smallBut if that is the case, I wonder why would you need these, because small clothes can be packed with big clothes, and then there are other bags that you can use for toiletries and accessories.Seriously, there is no point in spending the price. If you are looking to put away the clothes for special occasions (traditional) and stuff in the cupboard in away that they don’t catch dust, there are other big ones here on Amazon.
Bad quality product, one of the bags doesn't have a zip, and other one is torn
